: false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1743457855913508864/tEHZQQxF_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Joshua Hall", "username": "JoshHall2024"}, "content": "\ud83d\udea8BREAKING: \ud83d\udea8 FBI Director Kash Patel is reportedly preparing to formally announce FEDERAL CRIMINAL CHARGES against DISGRACED former President Barack Obama and DOZENS of other key individuals who were involved in the planning and execution of Russiagate in the aftermath of the", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 41212}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZHgo7ID", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 12, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8544395, "raw_content": "Stopping antibiotics early can allow remaining bacteria to survive, multiply, and potentially develop resistance, turning a treatable infection into a harder-to-manage one.  Healthcare providers emphasize completing the prescribed duration to ensure all harmful bacteria are eliminated and to prevent the recurrence of the infection. \n\nKey risks of not finishing a course include:\n\nInfection Recurrence: Symptoms may improve before the bacteria are fully eradicated, leading to a rebound infection that is more difficult to treat. \n\nAntibiotic Resistance: Surviving bacteria can mutate and become resistant to the medication, creating \"superbugs\" that are less responsive to standard treatments. \n\nPublic Health Impact: Resistant bacteria can spread to others, contributing to a global rise in infections that are challenging to cure. ", "author": "explodejoystick", "created": 1775646967918, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "CRASCH", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Completely random and not at all relevant information about antibiotics", "last_comment_created": 1775653389542, "content": "<p>Stopping antibiotics early can allow remaining bacteria to survive, multiply, and potentially develop resistance, turning a treatable infection into a harder-to-manage one.  Healthcare providers emphasize completing the prescribed duration to ensure all harmful bacteria are eliminated and to prevent the recurrence of the infection.</p>\n<p>Key risks of not finishing a course include:</p>\n<p>Infection Recurrence: Symptoms may improve before the bacteria are fully eradicated, leading to a rebound infection that is more difficult to treat.</p>\n<p>Antibiotic Resistance: Surviving bacteria can mutate and become resistant to the medication, creating &quot;superbugs&quot; that are less responsive to standard treatments.</p>\n<p>Public Health Impact: Resistant bacteria can spread to others, contributing to a global rise in infections that are challenging to cure.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 6, "score_up": 12, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2041704558930620632", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZHgoevR", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 9, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8544529, "raw_content": "", "author": "IlhansBrother", "created": 1775652567492, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "TheAftermath", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/